annotationA: Transcription factor IIEalpha (TfIIEalpha) is the large subunit of the RNA polymerase II general transcription factor TFIIE. TfIIEalpha, together with TfIIEbeta, is essential for transcription initiation in vitro and acts with RNA polymerase II and the other general transcription factors
annotationB: GEO11084p1; DNA binding; DNA-directed RNA polymerase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: transcription from RNA polymerase II promoter; transcription, DNA-templated
